<div id="review_3325635589" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3325635589" />
    <a title="Henrikas Kuryla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7062634-henrikas-kuryla"><img alt="Henrikas Kuryla" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1322462702p2/7062634.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3325635589?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Henrikas Kuryla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Henrikas Kuryla" href="/user/show/7062634-henrikas-kuryla">Henrikas Kuryla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3325635589" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8744769987842444218"><br/>This review contains spoilers.<br/><br/>The book is a journey through visions of a man in a coma. A central piece of those visions is The Bridge. In different fragments of dreams it reveals its different aspects: what it is bridging is unknown; is it a passage from life to death? or vice versa?; a passage through a high clear space between two shores teaming with aggressive life; it&apos;s a passage on which you carry out unclear mission which becomes even more unclear when you meet a mirror reflection of your</span>
  <span id="freeText8744769987842444218" style="display:none"><br />This review contains spoilers.<br /><br />The book is a journey through visions of a man in a coma. A central piece of those visions is The Bridge. In different fragments of dreams it reveals its different aspects: what it is bridging is unknown; is it a passage from life to death? or vice versa?; a passage through a high clear space between two shores teaming with aggressive life; it's a passage on which you carry out unclear mission which becomes even more unclear when you meet a mirror reflection of yourself moving in an opposite direction; dreams that are bridge or bridge that is a dream. The Bridge is a gigantic structure that is supposed to carry a stream of movement. But all the movement ceased, people established a city among constructions of the bridge and lead a stagnate life there. And it looks like nobody ever notices they are living on a bridge.<br />And then a symbolism of the lost library. It was supposed to have the information on the builders of a bridge and it's purpose. Lost memory? There are strange messages and it seems there is some force behind a scenes that makes it's best to prevent deciphering of those messages.<br />Then fragments of memories on the mans life start flowing in. The lifestory sounds like something that might become an obituary. And from that perspective this life seems rather dull. The different aspects of a bridge in the dream visions have their source in that lifestory. Random, mundane and devoid of any mysterious undertones.<br />Is The Bridge just an escape from this dullness of life in search for a deeper meaning?</span>
  <a data-text-id="8744769987842444218" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
