<div id="review_1711548214" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1711548214" />
    <a title="Nicky Neko" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26158987-nicky-neko"><img alt="Nicky Neko" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1394776682p2/26158987.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1711548214?book_show_action=true">Jul 28, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nicky Neko" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nicky Neko" href="/user/show/26158987-nicky-neko">Nicky Neko</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780349139210" href="/book/show/17465167-the-bridge">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1711548214" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2001919480298381127">Wow. What a crazy, ambitious book. Definitely not the kind of book an author could write as a debut. It seems to me that there are a ton of books and films that spin off from this work, and it&apos;s indicative of Banks&apos;s wild and creative imagination that he was coming up with this kind of stuff before anyone else. I could find all sorts of elements of things to come: tinges of <em>Inception</em>, <em>The Matrix</em>, Alex Garland&apos;s <em>The Coma</em>, even the transcription of Scottish dialect that would turn up in Irvine Wel</span>
  <span id="freeText2001919480298381127" style="display:none">Wow. What a crazy, ambitious book. Definitely not the kind of book an author could write as a debut. It seems to me that there are a ton of books and films that spin off from this work, and it's indicative of Banks's wild and creative imagination that he was coming up with this kind of stuff before anyone else. I could find all sorts of elements of things to come: tinges of <em>Inception</em>, <em>The Matrix</em>, Alex Garland's <em>The Coma</em>, even the transcription of Scottish dialect that would turn up in Irvine Welsh's <em>Trainspotting</em> several years later.<br /><br />This was a tough book to get into, but I'm so glad I persevered. It became something enormous, something brilliant and breathtaking, like the giant structure of the bridge itself. <br /><br />I still get a bit sentimental reading Iain Banks. I ration his books, and have been trying not read them all -- even more so since he died. Reading this one, I thought how sad it was that he died so young (59), but then I feel happy when I read sections of books like this from the 80s, and see evidence of his ebullience back then -- a quality which I don't think he ever lost. I really hope he lived his life like this quote, and had no regrets when he died:<br /><br /><em>Damn it I wanna </em>do<em> things! I want to travel the Trans-Siberian, go to India, stand on Ayers Rock, get sodden wet in Machupicchu! I want to surf! I </em>will<em> get a hang-glider; I want to go back to the Grand Canyon and get further than just the rim rock this time, I want to see the aurora borealis from Svalbard or Greenland, I want to see a total eclipse, I want to watch pyroclastic displays, I want to walk inside a lava tunnel, I want to see the earth from space, I want to drink </em>chang<em> in Ladakh, I want to cruise down the Amazon and up the Yangtze and walk the Great Wall; I want to visit Azania! I want to watch them push helicopters off the aircraft carriers again! </em>I want to be in bed with three women at once!<br /><br />And here's a quote we can probably all relate to:<br /><br /><em>No, I don't know where I am.<br />No, I don't know who I am.<br />Yes of course I know it's all a dream.<br />Isn't everything?</em></span>
  <a data-text-id="2001919480298381127" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


