<div id="review_116037108" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/116037108" />
    <a title="Stevelvis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/832410-stevelvis"><img alt="Stevelvis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627616694p2/832410.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/116037108?book_show_action=true">Aug 09, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stevelvis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stevelvis" href="/user/show/832410-stevelvis">Stevelvis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Banks fans</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Stevelvis by: </span>
      Iain M. Banks
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer116037108" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12494176997880049621">The first half of this book was a good 4-5 stars as the strange surroundings, characters and events were weaving into a mysterious dystopic surreality. Half way through as the weave tightens the mystery and strangeness slowly fades into a reflection of everyday reality and a sort of biography of a Scots life through the 1970s-1980s.<br/><br/>I&apos;ve already read all of Mr. Banks&apos; more challenging novels of science fiction, all of which I&apos;ve greatly enjoyed. The author has said that this is his favorite book </span>
  <span id="freeText12494176997880049621" style="display:none">The first half of this book was a good 4-5 stars as the strange surroundings, characters and events were weaving into a mysterious dystopic surreality. Half way through as the weave tightens the mystery and strangeness slowly fades into a reflection of everyday reality and a sort of biography of a Scots life through the 1970s-1980s.<br /><br />I've already read all of Mr. Banks' more challenging novels of science fiction, all of which I've greatly enjoyed. The author has said that this is his favorite book of those he's written and so my expectations may have been too high. I do recommend The Bridge, especially for Banks' fans, just don't expect a sci-fi masterpiece, and do enjoy the parts of it that are just that.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12494176997880049621" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

